title: Charming 1bd in Small Apartment Building Just a Block from Hamline U!
posting_body: ["This cozy unit features a bay window and recently installed hardwood style vinyl floors throughout the unit and you'll love cooking in the chic kitchen with updated cabinetry, stainless steel appliances and granite countertops.", 'Tenants enjoy on-site laundry, ample surface parking in the back, controlled access to the building, and 24/7 emergency maintenance.', 'Great location, directly across from Hancock Recreational Center/Hamline Elementary and 1 block from public transit bus stops, the thriving Snelling Ave business district, and Hamline University.', 'Utilities include: heat, water, trash, recycling, and sewage', 'Tenants are only responsible for electricity and cable/internet as desired.', 'Cat friendly.', 'One time pet deposit of $200 and no cat rent.', 'ESA animals welcome.', 'Application fee is $25 per adult tenant.', "Deposit is set based on application; range from $600-equivalent of first month's rent.", 'Rental requirements:', '2.5x monthly income as a combined household', '625+ credit score', 'Positive rental history.', 'No prior evictions/unlawful detainers.', 'No felonies', 'Sorry, we do not work with Section 8/GRH.', 'If this sounds like your ideal place, please reach out to Savannah by email or text/call at', 'show contact info']
